      "writtenOn": "2017-08-29T21:11:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "thanks for pointing this out; i didn\u0027t realize it did so much!\n\ni got this command from android (client/common_lib/cros/arc_common.py), but it looks like we\u0027re sleeping two seconds between each invocation there (which is a long time to wait). your suggestion seems like a good compromise.\n\ni\u0027ll probably need to make this a bit more complicated (i\u0027d like to watch the context instead of potentially looping forever). i\u0027ll test this more tomorrow and send an update then. (i am also suspicious of my \"!\u003d 1\" below, which appears backwards... :-/)\n\ni\u0027ll also mention that autotest of course has a second way of doing this in client/common_lib/cros/arc.py:\n\n  def is_android_booted():\n      \"\"\"Return whether Android has completed booting.\"\"\"\n      # We used to check sys.boot_completed system property to detect Android has\n      # booted in Android M, but in Android N it is set long before BOOT_COMPLETED\n      # intent is broadcast. So we read event logs instead.\n      log \u003d _android_shell(\n          \u0027logcat -d -b events *:S arc_system_event\u0027, ignore_status\u003dTrue)\n      return \u0027ArcAppLauncher:started\u0027 in log",
      "parentUuid": "0f436d3c_c4bf5f05",
